.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001677-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text from photographs\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>In detailed study of the theatre in 1986 this was the only inscription identified on the preserved seats. It is a reasonable assumption that since the same pair of letters is repeated, they have the same reference. The text on the vertical face of the seat (text B) is presented in the form of a monogram, with alpha much smaller and placed within the pi. The implication of the larger letters set out on the horizontal surface (text A) is that the small alpha should be read first in resolving such a monogrammatic presentation.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Isler 1986 29-30 with fig. 3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001915\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001915\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Large plain letters without serifs on the flat surface, smaller but similar on the vertical face; alpha is broad with a straight bar; pi has verticals of equal length and there is no extension of the horizontal beyond the verticals.\u003C/p> \u003Cp> Types list: \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type1.1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.1\u003C/a> \u003C/p> Line 1    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence \u003C/div>",[230,233,236,239,242,245,248,251],{"id":231,"html":232},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abA\">section A\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"divA--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"aA-l1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΠ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abB\">section B\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"divB--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"aB-l1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΠ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abA\">section A\u003C/span>\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"divA--diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"aA-l1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΠ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cspan clas